Definition: An acronym is an abbreviation formed from the initial letters of other words and pronounced as a word (e.g. ASCII, NASA). This task is about reading the given pre-tokenized setence and predict which token is an acronym. It is possible that the pre-tokenized sentence may contain more than one token as an acronym, in which case output the first acronym that you identify.
